<subSubSection id="8F8F6511FFB9FFC7C4DF00A19689F824" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C72A369AFFB9FFC7C4DF00A19689F824" blockId="14.[151,1437,1675,1990]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C4DF00A19464F90F" bold="true" box="[199,335,1747,1773]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C54000A197B6F90C" authority="Gajbe, 2004" authorityName="Gajbe" authorityYear="2004" box="[344,669,1747,1774]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haldanei">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C54000A19722F90F" box="[344,521,1747,1773]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Rhene haldanei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C60A00A197B6F90C" author="Gajbe, P. U." box="[530,669,1747,1774]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="1 - 154" refId="ref7358" refString="Gajbe, P. U. (2004) Spiders of Jabalpur, Madhya Pradesh (Arachnida: Araneae). Records of the Zoological Survey of India, Occasional Paper, 227, 1 - 154." type="journal article" year="2004">Gajbe, 2004</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a 
<typeStatus id="182E8838FFB9FFC7C7CB00A1911EF90F" box="[979,1077,1747,1773]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">holotype</typeStatus>
female from Jabalpur, 
<collectingRegion id="0551F878FFB9FFC7C15800A195D8F8F3" country="India" name="Madhya Pradesh" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Madhya Pradesh</collectingRegion>
. Detailed examination of the 
<typeStatus id="182E8838FFB9FFC7C621008597B0F8F3" box="[569,667,1783,1809]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">holotype</typeStatus>
revealed it to be identical to 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C7C4008A9189F8F3" authorityName="Zabka" authorityYear="1988" box="[988,1186,1783,1809]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulosus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C7C4008A9189F8F3" box="[988,1186,1783,1809]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Bianor angulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in both general colour pattern and genital morphology. The abdominal pattern with a pair of white spots in the posterior half and median chevron shaped markings; epigyne with a well-developed central pocket and fossae; copulatory openings leading to funnel-shaped inlets; copulatory ducts long with clearly visible first loop and spermathecae elongated (cf. 
<figureCitation id="5FAE2A1FFFB9FFC7C174011195F6F840" captionStart="FIGURES 65–71" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1180,1204]" captionTargetBox="[236,1355,196,1152]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[233,1355,181,1156]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 65–71. Somatic morphology and copulatory organs of Rhene haldanei Gajbe, 2004, holotype female: 65—habitus, dorsal view; 66—ditto, front view; 67—ditto, lateral view; 68—leg I, retrolateral view; 69—epigyne, ventral view; 70—vulva, dorsal view; 71—label. Scale bars: (69, 70) 0.2 mm, (66) 0.5 mm, (65, 68) 1 mm, (67) 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450941/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Figs 65–70</figureCitation>
with figs 7, 11 in 
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C5BD01F59717F840" author="Zabka, M." box="[421,572,1927,1954]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="197 - 485" refId="ref8837" refString="Zabka, M. (1985) Systematic and zoogeographic study on the family Salticidae (Araneae) from Viet-Nam. Annales Zoologici, Warszawa, 39, 197 - 485." type="journal article" year="1985">Zabka (1985)</bibRefCitation>
and figs 53, 55, 
<quantity id="006D9B7FFFB9FFC7C6ED01F59606F843" box="[757,813,1927,1953]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5493999999999999" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" unit="in" value="61.0">61 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="A3044B6BFFB9FFC7C72C01FA96DCF840" author="Logunov, D. V." box="[820,1015,1928,1954]" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" pagination="221 - 286" refId="ref7571" refString="Logunov, D. V. (2001) A redefinition of the genera Bianor Peckham &amp; Peckham, 1885 and Harmochirus Simon, 1885, with the establishment of a new genus Sibianor gen. n. (Aranei: Salticidae). Arthropoda Selecta, 9, 221 - 286." type="journal article" year="2001">Logunov (2001))</bibRefCitation>
. Thus, the species 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C0DD01FA906DF843" authorityName="Gajbe" authorityYear="2004" box="[1221,1350,1927,1953]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Rhene" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="haldanei">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C0DD01FA906DF843" box="[1221,1350,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">R. haldanei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is to be treated as a member of 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C58501DE94C0F827" box="[413,491,1964,1989]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C58501DE94C0F827" box="[413,491,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">Bianor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="00954D19FFB9FFC7C71301DE96B7F827" authorityName="Zabka" authorityYear="1988" box="[779,924,1963,1989]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bianor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulosus">
<emphasis id="F5E1EA88FFB9FFC7C71301DE96B7F827" box="[779,924,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="403">B. angulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
